<doc id="1038041" wikidata="Q17025887" url="?curid=1038041" title="Misty Eyed Adventures">
<text>Misty Eyed Adventures is a music album by Irish musician Máire Brennan, now known as &quot;Moya Brennan&quot;. This was the second solo outing for her and features many of her family and friends on the recording. It was released in 1995.

Recordings were made in Scotland during 1995:

*Castle Sound Studio, Pencaitland, Scotland – (Engineer Calum Malcolm)
Additional recordings
*Windmill Lane Studios, Dublin, Ireland – (Engineer Charles Byrne) (for &quot;Big Yellow Taxi&quot;)
*Barrymore Studios, Co. Clare, Ireland – (Engineer Colin Boland) (for &quot;A Place Among The Stones&quot;)

