<doc id="1038111" wikidata="Q2844168" url="?curid=1038111" title="Amphibian Airplanes of Canada">
<text>Amphibian Airplanes of Canada (AAC) is a developer and marketer of light amphibious aircraft based in Squamish, British Columbia.

AAC was established by Hans Schaer in Squamish, British Columbia in 1998 to develop a light amphibious aircraft to be marketed for homebuilding.

== Aircraft ==
* AAC SeaStar
* AAC Seastar Sealoon

