<text>In mathematics, an Euler–Cauchy equation, or Cauchy–Euler equation, or simply Euler&#x27;s equation, is a linear homogeneous ordinary differential equation with variable coefficients. It is sometimes referred to as an &quot;equidimensional&quot; equation. Because of its particularly simple equidimensional structure, the differential equation can be solved explicitly.

